description:
Add HideOnFocusLost option to WebviewWindowOptions.

Files to modify:
- webview_window_options.go: Add HideOnFocusLost bool field
- webview_window.go: Implement focus-lost handler in setupBehaviorOptions()
- linux_cgo.go: GTK3 focus-lost signal (focus-out-event)
- linux_cgo_gtk4.go: GTK4 focus-lost signal (notify::is-active)
- webview_window_darwin.go: macOS focus-lost handling
- webview_window_windows.go: Windows focus-lost handling

Platform behavior:
- Standard WMs: Hide on focus lost
- Focus-follows-mouse WMs (Hyprland, Sway, i3): Silently disabled

Implementation:
if options.HideOnFocusLost {
    if runtime.GOOS == "linux" && isFocusFollowsMouse() {
        return // Skip - would cause immediate hide
    }
    w.OnWindowEvent(events.Common.WindowLostFocus, func(e *WindowEvent) {
        w.Hide()
    })
}

Add HideOnEscape option to WebviewWindowOptions.

Files to modify:
- webview_window_options.go: Add HideOnEscape bool field
- webview_window.go: Register Escape keybinding in setupBehaviorOptions()

Implementation:
if options.HideOnEscape {
    w.registerKeyBinding("escape", func() {
        w.Hide()
    })
}

Notes:
- Should work on all platforms (GTK3, GTK4, macOS, Windows)
- Uses existing keybinding infrastructure

Implement smart defaults for systray click behavior.

Smart Defaults:
| Configuration | Left-Click | Right-Click |
|--------------|------------|-------------|
| Window only | ToggleWindow | Nothing |
| Menu only | Nothing | ShowMenu |
| Window + Menu | ToggleWindow | ShowMenu |
| Neither | Nothing | Nothing |

Files to modify:
- systemtray.go: Add applySmartDefaults() method, call from Run()

Implementation:
func (s *SystemTray) applySmartDefaults() {
    hasWindow := s.attachedWindow.Window != nil
    hasMenu := s.menu != nil

    if s.clickHandler == nil {
        if hasWindow {
            s.clickHandler = s.ToggleWindow
        }
    }

    if s.rightClickHandler == nil {
        if hasMenu {
            s.rightClickHandler = s.ShowMenu
        }
    }
}

User-specified OnLeftClick/OnRightClick handlers override these defaults.
